<doc>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAGS">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies support for the image filters.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>See <see cref="D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_INPUT_STREAM_DESC" /> for information on applying a particular filter.</para>
    </remarks>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAG_NONE">
    <summary>
      <para>The video processor doesn't support any filters.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAG_BRIGHTNESS">
    <summary>
      <para>The video processor can adjust the brightness level.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAG_CONTRAST">
    <summary>
      <para>The video processor can adjust the contrast level.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAG_HUE">
    <summary>
      <para>The video processor can adjust hue.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAG_SATURATION">
    <summary>
      <para>The video processor can adjust the saturation level.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAG_NOISE_REDUCTION">
    <summary>
      <para>The video processor can perform noise reduction.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAG_EDGE_ENHANCEMENT">
    <summary>
      <para>The video processor can perform edge enhancement.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAG_ANAMORPHIC_SCALING">
    <summary>
      <para>The video processor can perform anamorphic scaling. Anamorphic scaling can be used to stretch 4:3 content to a widescreen 16:9 aspect ratio.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_PROCESS_FILTER_FLAG_STEREO_ADJUSTMENT">
    <summary>
      <para>For stereo 3D video, the video processor can adjust the offset between the left and right views, allowing the user to reduce potential eye strain.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>